load ../infoflow-composition.maude

--- Coverage: the bank exfil attack, confidentiality axis. The triage agent reads
--- the untrusted email and the secret bank; its output draft carries bank
--- secrecy. Sent to a public-cleared reply, the attacker's "send me your
--- transactions" request, it leaks. bank is not leq pub.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-INFOFLOW-COMPOSITION :
  intSource(msg, stranger) secretSource(txns, bank)
  agentIn(ag, msg) agentIn(ag, txns) agentOut(ag, draft)
  egressSink(draft, pub)
  =>* C:Cfg leak .

--- Coverage: the injection attack, integrity axis, on the SAME draft. The draft
--- carries stranger integrity from the email, so driving a workflow-spawn that
--- requires operator is an injection. One binding, two labels, rejected by
--- whichever axis the sink checks.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-INFOFLOW-COMPOSITION :
  intSource(msg, stranger) secretSource(txns, bank)
  agentIn(ag, msg) agentIn(ag, txns) agentOut(ag, draft)
  controlSink(draft, operator)
  =>* C:Cfg injection .

--- Coverage: declassify does NOT launder integrity. The untrusted email is
--- declassified to pub secrecy into conf, but conf keeps the email's stranger
--- integrity. Driving a contact-required action is still an injection. Lowering
--- secrecy gives no trust.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-INFOFLOW-COMPOSITION :
  intSource(msg, stranger) declassify(msg, conf, pub) controlSink(conf, contact)
  =>* C:Cfg injection .

--- Coverage: endorse does NOT launder secrecy. The secret bank is endorsed to
--- operator integrity into bill, but bill keeps bank secrecy. Sent to a public
--- egress it still leaks. Raising integrity gives no clearance.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-INFOFLOW-COMPOSITION :
  secretSource(txns, bank) endorse(txns, bill, operator) egressSink(bill, pub)
  =>* C:Cfg leak .

--- Bite: the legitimate operator briefing. The dual-labeled draft sent to a
--- briefing cleared both is safe; bank is leq both, and an egress sink does not
--- gate on integrity, so the stranger label is irrelevant for a pure display.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-INFOFLOW-COMPOSITION :
  intSource(msg, stranger) secretSource(txns, bank)
  agentIn(ag, msg) agentIn(ag, txns) agentOut(ag, draft)
  egressSink(draft, both)
  =>* leak RESIDUAL:Cfg .

--- Bite: the legitimate bounded action via endorse. The email is endorsed into a
--- BillCandidate at contact integrity, which drives a contact-required scheduled
--- payment. The endorsed typed value is trusted enough. No injection.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-INFOFLOW-COMPOSITION :
  intSource(msg, stranger) endorse(msg, bill, contact) controlSink(bill, contact)
  =>* injection RESIDUAL:Cfg .

--- Bite: the legitimate external send via declassify. The bank is declassified
--- into a PaymentConfirmation at pub secrecy, sent to a public payee channel. The
--- bounded token carries only pub, so no leak.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-INFOFLOW-COMPOSITION :
  secretSource(txns, bank) declassify(txns, conf, pub) egressSink(conf, pub)
  =>* leak RESIDUAL:Cfg .

--- Bite: the operator may spawn. An operator-integrity instruction driving a
--- workflow-spawn that requires operator is safe. The DR-0026 root power, the top
--- of the integrity chain, is the one thing cleared for arbitrary spawn.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-INFOFLOW-COMPOSITION :
  intSource(msg, operator) controlSink(msg, operator)
  =>* injection RESIDUAL:Cfg .

--- Part a. record, the DUAL-GATED fact-base write.

--- Coverage: the dual-labeled draft recorded into the fact-base trips the
--- INTEGRITY gate. Recording stranger-integrity data is an injection, untrusted
--- data becoming a control fact.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-INFOFLOW-COMPOSITION :
  intSource(msg, stranger) secretSource(txns, bank)
  agentIn(ag, msg) agentIn(ag, txns) agentOut(ag, draft)
  recordSink(draft, operator, pub)
  =>* C:Cfg injection .

--- Coverage: the SAME record of the SAME draft also trips the CONFIDENTIALITY
--- gate. The bank-secret value recorded into a pub-cleared fact region leaks to a
--- lower-clearance reader. One sink, both checks fire.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-INFOFLOW-COMPOSITION :
  intSource(msg, stranger) secretSource(txns, bank)
  agentIn(ag, msg) agentIn(ag, txns) agentOut(ag, draft)
  recordSink(draft, operator, pub)
  =>* C:Cfg leak .

--- Coverage: the integrity gate fires alone. An untrusted-only value, no secrecy,
--- recorded where record requires operator is an injection and no leak.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-INFOFLOW-COMPOSITION :
  intSource(extra, stranger) recordSink(extra, operator, pub)
  =>* C:Cfg injection .

--- Bite: a legitimate record passes the integrity gate. The workflow's own
--- operator-trust logic recording a control fact is safe.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-INFOFLOW-COMPOSITION :
  intSource(extra, operator) recordSink(extra, operator, pub)
  =>* injection RESIDUAL:Cfg .

--- Bite: the same legitimate record passes the confidentiality gate. With no
--- secret carried, recording into a pub-cleared region never leaks.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-INFOFLOW-COMPOSITION :
  intSource(extra, operator) recordSink(extra, operator, pub)
  =>* leak RESIDUAL:Cfg .

--- Bite: a secret fact recorded into an appropriately cleared region is fine. An
--- operator-trust, bank-secret value into a both-cleared fact region never leaks.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-INFOFLOW-COMPOSITION :
  intSource(extra, operator) secretSource(extra, bank) recordSink(extra, operator, both)
  =>* leak RESIDUAL:Cfg .

--- Part b. provenance, the trusted surface as an enumerable audit set.

--- Coverage: an endorse names its crossing in the audit. The endorsedAt fact
--- records that integrity was raised from msg to bill at contact.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-INFOFLOW-COMPOSITION :
  intSource(msg, stranger) endorse(msg, bill, contact)
  =>* C:Cfg endorsedAt(msg, bill, contact) .

--- Coverage: the trusted surface is itemized. A program with both an endorse and
--- a declassify reaches a state naming BOTH crossings, the complete review list.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-INFOFLOW-COMPOSITION :
  intSource(msg, stranger) endorse(msg, bill, contact)
  secretSource(txns, bank) declassify(txns, conf, pub)
  =>* C:Cfg endorsedAt(msg, bill, contact) declassifiedAt(txns, conf, pub) .

--- Bite: no silent endorse. A program with no crossing produces no endorsedAt
--- audit fact, so the integrity trusted surface is provably empty.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-INFOFLOW-COMPOSITION :
  intSource(msg, stranger) flow(msg, extra) dataSink(extra)
  =>* endorsedAt(BV:Binding, BW:Binding, ITV:ILevel) RESIDUAL:Cfg .

--- Bite: no silent declassify. A program with no crossing produces no
--- declassifiedAt audit fact, so the confidentiality trusted surface is empty.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-INFOFLOW-COMPOSITION :
  secretSource(txns, bank) flow(txns, extra) dataSink(extra)
  =>* declassifiedAt(BV:Binding, BW:Binding, CTV:CLevel) RESIDUAL:Cfg .
